    Relative Weight to determine the reimbursement amount on a per case basis.';

--
-- Name: COLUMN insurance_plan_main.gap_amount; Type: COMMENT; Schema: fresh; Owner: -
--

COMMENT ON COLUMN insurance_plan_main.gap_amount IS 'Gap is the segment of cost to be borne
    by the provider that is above the calculated DRG
    reimbursement amount before the account becomes eligible for an outlier payment.
    It is a set amount that should be reviewed periodically in conjunction with
    updates to the base rate by the facility.';

--
-- Name: COLUMN insurance_plan_main.marginal_percent; Type: COMMENT; Schema: fresh; Owner: -
--

COMMENT ON COLUMN insurance_plan_main.marginal_percent IS 'Marginal Percent is the established percentage
    applied to the Costs above the Base Rate plus the Gap
    that will be reimbursed to a provider as the outlier payment.
    If the sum of the Base Rate plus the Gap equal more than the total Costs,
    there is no provision for an outlier payment.';

